<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1752,1934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,302,1752,1778]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Etymology:</emphasis>
—Since the name 
<taxonomicName authority="(Haworth 1804: 7) Haworth (1812: 82)" authorityName="Haworth" authorityPageNumber="82" authorityYear="1812" baseAuthorityName="Haworth" baseAuthorityPageNumber="7" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[532,1194,1753,1779]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolia">
<emphasis box="[532,696,1753,1778]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Aloe latifolia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haworth, A. H." box="[714,928,1753,1779]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref5323" refString="Haworth, A. H. (1804) A new arrangement of the genus Aloe. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London 7: 1 - 28. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1804. tb 00276. x" type="journal article" year="1804">Haworth 1804: 7</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Haworth, A. H." box="[947,1194,1753,1779]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" refId="ref5374" refString="Haworth, A. H. (1812) Synopsis Plantarum Succulentarum. Taylor, London, 207 pp." type="book" year="1812">Haworth (1812: 82)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
already exists, this combination is not available for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zonneveld &amp; Fritz" authorityYear="2010" box="[540,814,1792,1817]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Chortolirion" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolium">
<emphasis box="[540,814,1792,1817]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Chortolirion latifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The new name commemorates Barbara Joan Jeppe (1921–1999), who wrote and illustrated a book on the aloes of 
<collectingCountry box="[953,1114,1830,1856]" name="South Africa" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jeppe, B." box="[1132,1278,1830,1856]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" refId="ref5418" refString="Jeppe, B. (1969) South African Aloes. Purnell, Cape Town, 150 pp." type="book" year="1969">Jeppe 1969</bibRefCitation>
) that is now considered to be valuable historical literature on the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, G. F. &amp; Steyn, E. M. A." box="[846,1092,1869,1895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" pagination="119 - 122" refId="ref5906" refString="Smith, G. F. &amp; Steyn, E. M. A. (2000) Barbara Joan Jeppe (1921 - 1999): botanical artist extraordinaire. Bothalia 30: 119 - 122." type="journal article" year="2000">Smith &amp; Steyn 2000</bibRefCitation>
). Despite her contributions to illustrating the aloes of 
<collectingCountry box="[427,581,1908,1934]" name="South Africa" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, she has never been commemorated in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1159,1212,1908,1933]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1159,1212,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Aloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
